  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a biomedical, open label, therapeutic strategy, interventional, non-randomized,
      multicenter study to evaluate the non compliance to antimalarials in patients with systemic
      lupus in the Nord Pas-de-Calais region (FRANCE). It is conducted in two visits. These visits
      consist in obtaining blood sample, performing a clinical examination and filling in a
      questionnaire (Quality Of Life, Coping...).

      The goal for the noncompliants patients is to guide them towards the therapeutic education
      with professionals (nurses and physicians).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
